Initiative The California Rural Policy Task Force The Local Government Partnership VitalCommInitiative shtml The Vital Communities Initiative Beginning in March of 2002 OPR embarked on a new program for the support of local communities and their community development efforts The Vital Communities Initiative provides a broad framework for state agencies to undertake core mission related community development activities in a more collaborative and integrated fashion RuralPolicy shtml The California Rural Policy Task Force In October of 2001 OPR convened the first meeting of the California Rural Policy Task Force Task Force with the purpose of improving program and service delivery of State resources to rural areas Monthly Task Force meetings provide State agencies and departments with an opportunity to develop collaborative solutions to better meeting the needs of rural communities Partnership shtml The Local Government Partnership The Local Government Partnership Partnership was established in the Summer of 2001 to improve the interaction between state and local governments The Partnership provides a forum for high level policy discussions and rapid disemination of information on key community development issues including energy terrorism preparedness environmental protection and housing Community Vitalization Unit Team Members Toni Symonds Director Community Vitalization Unit Director California Rural Policy Task Force mailto toni symonds opr ca gov toni symonds opr ca gov Kathryn Winter Deputy Director Community Vitalization Unit Executive Director Local Government Partnership mailto kathryn winter opr ca gov kathryn winter opr ca gov Diane Padilla Assistant Director Vital Communities Initiative mailto diane padilla opr ca gov diane padilla opr ca gov James Lanas Federal Partners Coordinator Vital Communities Initiative mailto jim lanas opr ca gov jim lanas opr ca gov Related Links Accomplishments shtml Davis Administration Rural Accomplishments Governor Gray Davis